Janet M. ThomasProfessor Emeritus, EconomicsDirector, Framingham State University Foundation, Inc.Ph.D., Boston College, 1987M.A., Boston College, 1985
Office: Morison Hall 114
|  781.891._2053 | 
jthomas@bentley.edu
Department Phone: 781.891._2053
| Department Fax: 781.891.2896                       



Expand All
Collapse All
Bio
Has researched actively in applied microeconomics, corporate social responsibility, executive compensation, environmental economics, and sports economics. Teaching fields have included intermediate price theory and environmental economics. Publications have appeared in journals such as Land Economics, the Southern Economic Journal, The Review of Industrial Organization, and the Journal of Sports Economics. Is the co-author of Environmental Economics and Management, a textbook for undergraduate and MBA students, now in its 6th edition. Is the recipient of the Faculty Member of the Year Award (1991), Adamian Award for Teaching Excellence (1993), the Scholar of the Year Award (1996), and the Outstanding Scholarly Contribution Award (2005).
Teaching Interests
Intermediate Price Theory;
Environmental Economics and Management;
Industrial Organization and Markets;
Principles of Economics
Research Interests
Applied Microeconomics;
Environmental Economics and Management; Corporate Social Responsibility;
CEO Compensation;
Industrial Organization and Markets;
Sports Economics;
Cost Analysis;
Consulting/Practice Interests
Environmental Economics;
Corporate Social Responsibility;
Cost Analysis;
Price and Nonprice Competitive Strategies
